10 Real-Life AI Applications I Use Daily

Google Maps
It uses machine learning to study traffic, road conditions, and past travel data to suggest the best route and estimate travel time.

Google Assistant
ML helps it understand my voice commands and get better at answering based on how I use it over time.

Instagram
It learns from what I like, comment on, or watch to show posts and reels that match my interests.

YouTube
Machine learning recommends videos by tracking my watch history, searches, and viewing time.

Spotify
It studies my listening habits to suggest songs and playlists I’m likely to enjoy.

Gmail
ML helps filter spam and organize emails by learning from email content and my actions.

Amazon
It predicts what products I might like based on what I search, view, and buy.

Netflix
Machine learning analyzes what I watch to recommend movies and shows that suit my taste.

Google Photos
ML recognizes faces, places, and objects to automatically organize and search my photos.

Phone Face Unlock
It uses machine learning to recognize my face and unlock the phone securely, even with small changes in appearance.